Krishna University In-Charge Vice-Chancellor D. Suryachandra Rao on Wednesday said that the construction works of the university’s new academic block would begin by January end on its own site at Rudravaram village near Machilipatnam.Addressing senate members of Krishna University here at the fourth academic senate meet here, Mr. Suryachandra Rao said that the construction works of the administrative block would begin in February.New buildingsThe university has signed a Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) with the Central Public Works Department (CPWD) for construction of the university’s own buildings.Former KRU Vice-Chancellors Mr. Durga Prasad, V. Venkaiah and Mr. Viyyanna Rao offered their comments on the existing research projects and research being done by various departments.In-camera meetMeanwhile, the KRU authorities on Wednesday held the fourth academic senate meeting without letting the media cover the proceedings.The meeting was held in camera reportedly because of fear of differences among the teaching staff members on various academic and research issues getting exposed. Incidentally, this was the first in-camera academic senate meet held in Machilipatnam.University has signed MoU with Central Public Works Dept. for construction of buildings